---
import { Image } from "@astrojs/image/components";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import MainHeader from "../../components/Tags/MainHeader.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Tags/Section.astro";
import Paragraph from "../../components/Tags/Paragraph.astro";
import Heading3 from "../../components/Tags/Heading3.astro";
import Sponsors from "../../components/Sponsors.astro";
import UList from "../../components/Tags/UList.astro";
import List from "../../components/Tags/List.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Calls :: AVSS2023"
  meta="Details about Call for Challenges. The important dates are May 1, 2023 (Challenge Workshop Proposal Submission), May 15, 2023 (Acceptance Notification), and November 6, 2023 (Challenge Date)."
>
  <MainHeader metaTitle="Calls" title="Calls For Challenges" />
  <Section>
    <section class="-mx-4 rounded-md bg-red-100 px-4 py-4 text-red-800">
      <p class="font-bold italic">
        19th IEEE Int. Conf. on Advanced Video and Signal-Based Surveillance
      </p>
      <p class="font-bold italic">
        Both at EXCO Convention Center, Daegu, South Korea and virtually.
      </p>
      <p class="font-bold italic">6 (Mon.) ~ 9 (Thur.), November, 2023</p>
    </section>

    <Paragraph>
      <strong>AVSS 2023</strong> is the <strong>19th</strong> edition of the
      <strong>
        IEEE International Conference on Advanced Video and Signal-Based
        Surveillance,
      </strong>
      a premier forum for the presentation of new advances and research results in
      the field of video and signal-based surveillance. AVSS 2023 is
      <strong> sponsored by the IEEE Signal Processing Society.</strong>
      The goal is to provide a game-changing and cross-disciplinary forum that brings
      together experts from academia, industry, and government to advance the frontiers
      of theories, methods, systems, and applications.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      AVSS 2023 invites proposals for Challenge addressing problems that will
      engage and excite the video processing/analytics and surveillance research
      community.
    </Paragraph>
    <Heading3 title="Important Dates" />
    <figure>
      <table
        class="w-full max-w-2xl table-auto border-gray-600 text-xl font-bold"
      >
        <tbody class="border-2 border-gray-600">
          <tr class="border-y-2 border-gray-600 odd:bg-gray-200">
            <td class="border-x-2 border-gray-600 px-4 py-4"
              >Challenge Workshop Proposal Submission Deadline</td
            >
            <td class="px-4 py-4">May 1, 2023</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-y-2 border-gray-600 odd:bg-gray-200">
            <td class="border-x-2 border-gray-600 px-4 py-4"
              >Acceptance Notification</td
            >
            <td class="px-4 py-4">May 15, 2023</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-y-2 border-gray-600 odd:bg-gray-200">
            <td class="border-x-2 border-gray-600 px-4 py-4">Challenge Date</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-4">November 6, 2023</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </figure>
    <Paragraph>
      The proposal should include the following information:
    </Paragraph>
    <UList>
      <List>
        The challenge title that is explicative of the addressed topic
      </List>
      <List>A brief introduction of the challenge (max 500 words)</List>
      <List>
        The impact and significance of the challeng in the research and/or
        industrial community
      </List>
      <List>The rules for participation</List>
      <List>
        The criteria that will be used to evaulate the submitted entries
      </List>
      <List>The team that will run the challenge</List>
      <List>
        Important dates (e.g., submission deadline, data available, and winner
        anouncement)
      </List>
      <List>Award propsed (if any)</List>
      <List>Sponsorship (if any)</List>
    </UList>
    <Paragraph>
      Challenge organizers should provide a dataset to participating teams that
      should include <em>a training set with ground truth</em> and a <em
        >testing set whose ground truth is hidden</em
      >. Challenge organizers are in charge of the evaluating the results/models
      submitted by the participants on the testing set.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      Challenge organizers will also organize the presentation of the
      best-performing teams in a dedicated session at AVSS. The session
      includes:
    </Paragraph>

    <UList>
      <List>The presentation of the challenge</List>
      <List>The presentation of awards and the sponsors (if any)</List>
      <List>
        A presentation of the model/approach by the participating teams
      </List>
    </UList>

    <Heading3 title="Submission Instructions" />
    <Paragraph>
      Proposals should be submitted via email to the challenge chairs:
    </Paragraph>
    <UList>
      <List>
        Zheng Tang (Nvidia Metropolis, USA) : <a
          class="fancy"
          href="mailto:tangzhengthomas@gmail.com">tangzhengthomas@gmail.com</a
        >
      </List>
      <List>
        Weiyao Lin (SJTU, China) : <a
          class="fancy"
          href="mailto:wylin@sjtu.edu.cn">wylin@sjtu.edu.cn</a
        >
      </List>
    </UList>

    <Paragraph>
      Inquiries regarding the challenge sessions should be sent to the challenge
      chairs.
    </Paragraph>
    <Sponsors />
  </Section>
</Layout>
